A 51-year-old mother   fought off an intruder after finding him standing over her young daughter.

Fiona, 51, said she knew the assailant had 'picked the wrong lady' as she became overwhelmed with maternal instincts and pushed him from her Perth home on Thursday night. 

'I said, 'It's all right, stay there' and I rushed him,' she told Nine News.

