She said seeing her child in danger gave her a boost of courage.  

'When it's your child, you don't think of that.

'It's not brave, it's just what you do,' she added.

Fiona said she and a friend were initially concerned after hearing someone cutting into the fly screen at her front door.

She said when she saw the man, standing with his hand raised over her daughter's head, she pushed him, forcing him down the hall way.

